    "youtube" : "",
    "ingredients" : "<ul><li>2 lbs. Tanigue (Wahoo fish), fillet and cut into cubes</li><li>2 thumbs fresh ginger, minced</li><li>8 pieces hot chili (Thai chili or siling labuyo), chopped</li><li>15 to 20 pieces calamansi</li><li>1 medium red onion, chopped into small pieces</li><li>¼ teaspoon ground black pepper</li><li>½ teaspoon sugar</li><li>Salt to taste</li></ul>",
